py` – Dry-run: fake images → patches → integer-FFT + QA residues.\n* `config.example.json` – paths + knobs. Copy to `config.json` and edit.\n\nRun quick dry-runs (no datasets needed):\n\n```bash\npython arc_runner.py --dry_run\npython gsm8k_runner.py --dry_run\npython imagenet_qafeatures.py --dry_run\n```\n\n# Strong baselines \u0026 ablations (do these first)\n\n1. **Linear vs MLP** on QA features\n\n* Train logreg and a 2×128 MLP on output of QA featureizers.\n* If linear already carries signal, QA features are doing real work.\n\n2. **Residues only vs +DFT vs +tuples**\n\n* (A) mod-24 histograms only\n* (B) A + integer power spectrum\n* (C) A+B + canonical (b,e,d,a) invariants\n  This isolates which QA component carries the lift.\n\n3. **Prime-sector masking**\n\n* Keep only residues in {±1,±5,±7,±11} vs all 24: tests icositetragonal hypothesis.\n\n4. **Backbone + QA head** (optional)\n\n* Freeze a pretrained model; feed its pooled features concatenated with QA features; train a tiny head. If the head improves over backbone alone, QA adds complementary structure.\n\n# Success criteria (tight, measurable)\n\n* **ARC:** +X% tasks solved over a rule-free baseline at equal search budget.\n* **GSM8K/MATH:** exact-match gain, but also report “**rational-equivalent**” (e.g., 6/8 \u003d\u003d 3/4).\n* **HumanEval:** pass@1 and pass@10 re-ranking lift.\n* **ImageNet:** top-1 and robustness: QA head should be less brittle on ImageNet-A/O subsets.\n\n# Where to plug your real datasets\n\nCopy `config.example.json` → `config.json` and set paths:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"arc_dir\": \"/path/to/ARC/\",\n    \"gsm8k_file\": \"/path/to/gsm8k/train.jsonl\",\n    \"math_dir\": \"/path/to/MATH/\",\n    \"humaneval_file\": \"/path/to/HumanEval.jsonl\",\n    \"imagenet_dir\": \"/path/to/imagenet/\"\n  },\n  \"output_dir\": \"./outputs\",\n  \"imagenet\": {\"patch_size\": 16, \"stride\": 16, \"max_images\": 16},\n  \"qa\": {\"fft_window\": 32, \"use_mod24\": true}\n}\n```\n