arch papers\u0027 pages (e.g., [ImageNet-A](https://github.com/hendrycks/natural-adv-examples), [ImageNet-O](https://github.com/hendrycks/imagenet-o)).\n    *   **`imagenet_dir` in `config.json`:** Point this to the root directory where your ImageNet (or Tiny ImageNet) images are stored (e.g., `/path/to/imagenet/`).\n\n**General Steps to Set Up:**\n\n1.  **Create `config.json`:** Copy `config.example.json` to `config.json`.\n    ```bash\n    cp config.example.json config.json\n    ```\n2.  **Download Datasets:** Go to the links above and download the datasets.\n3.  **Update `config.json`:** Edit `config.json` to point the `paths` to the actual locations on your system where you\u0027ve downloaded and extracted these datasets.\n\nOnce you have the datasets downloaded and your `config.json` updated, you should be able to run the full evaluation scripts (by omitting the `--dry_run` flag).\n\nLet me know if you have trouble finding or setting up any specific dataset!",
